<subSubSection box="[199,1038,799,824]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,1038,799,824]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,799,824]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">Etymology</emphasis>
. Latin, 
<taxonomicName box="[413,508,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cicatrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicolor">
<emphasis box="[413,508,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">unicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
= with single color; relating to the elytra color.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="279" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,836,861]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[323,533,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cicatrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicolor">
<emphasis box="[323,533,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">Cicatrion unicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Martins &amp; Napp, 1986" authorityName="Martins &amp; Napp" authorityYear="1986" box="[685,1075,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cicatrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calidum">
<emphasis box="[685,809,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">C. calidum</emphasis>
Martins &amp; Napp, 
<number box="[1019,1075,836,861]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</taxonomicName>
as follows: pronotum distinctly punctate; elytra without yellowish elliptical spot. In 
<taxonomicName box="[751,876,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cicatrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calidum">
<emphasis box="[751,876,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">C. calidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the pronotum is slightly punctate and the elytra have yellowish elliptical spot. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Martins, 1962" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1962" box="[660,1036,908,933]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cicatrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constricticolle">
<emphasis box="[660,852,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">C. constricticolle</emphasis>
(Martins, 
<number box="[971,1028,908,933]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279" value="1962.0">1962</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
by the pronotum with longitudinal, slightly distinct sulcus in males, and by the elytra without yellowish elliptical spot. In 
<taxonomicName box="[1185,1382,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cicatrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constricticolle">
<emphasis box="[1185,1382,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">C. constricticolle</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the longitudinal sulcus is well-distinct in males and the elytra have yellowish elliptical spot.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1070,1052,1077]" box="[151,1070,1052,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">
The new species can be inserted in key to species from 
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" box="[772,941,1052,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279" refString="Martins, U. R. (2009) Tribo Ibidionini, Subtribo Compsina, p. In: Martins, U. R. (org.). Cerambycidae Sul-Americanos (Coleoptera). Taxonomia. Vol. 10. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. vii + 1 - 199." type="book chapter" year="2009">
Martins (
<number box="[874,933,1052,1076]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279" value="2009.0">2009</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as follows:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
